{
  "texts": [
    "We need to show that if ∀Z ∈ P, x ∈ ⊠ i Z ⇒ y ∈ Z, then xR i y.",
    "Suppose that we do not have xR i y, so there is a y′ ∈ A with ⊥ ̸ = y ′ ≤ y and x ∧ ♦ i y ′ = ⊥.",
    "Then we claim that x ∈ ⊠ i ↓-y ′, i.e., R i (x) ⊆ ↓-y ′.",
    "If xR i v, then for all v ′ ∈ A such that ⊥ ̸ = v ′ ≤ v, we have x ∧ ♦ i v ′ ̸ = ⊥, which with x ∧ ♦ i y ′ = ⊥ implies v ′ ̸ ≤ y ′.",
    "Since this holds for all v ′ ̸ = ⊥ with v ′ ≤ v, we have v ≤ -y ′."
  ]
}